Executive Profile
Edith E. Holiday  Independent Director, Hess CorporationAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 43 Board Members in 43 different organizations across 48 different industries.See Board Relationships65$305,264
Background

		Ms. Edith E. Holiday, also known as Ede, served as the Chief Counsel and National Financial and Operations Director for the George Bush National Presidential Campaign and Political Organization from 1985 to 1988. Ms. Holiday served as an Assistant to the President of the United States and Secretary of the Cabinet from 1990 to early 1993, General Counsel to the United States Department of Treasury from 1989 to 1990 and Counselor to a Secretary and Assistant Secretary ... for Public Affairs and Public Liaison from 1988 to 1989. Since 1984, she served as an Executive Director of the President's Commission on Executive, Legislative and Judicial Salaries. During Regan administration, she was the Chief Spokesman for the Treasury Department. Since 1982, she served as the Chief Legislative Advisor and Policy Aide to the United States Senator Nicholas F. Brady. She worked for the law firm of Dow, Lohner & Albertson in Atlanta from 1983 to 1984 and for Reed, Smith, Shaw & McClay from 1977 to 1983. She has been an Independent Director of White Mountains Insurance Group Ltd. since August 26, 2004 and H.J. Heinz Company since 1994. She has been Lead Independent Trustee at Templeton Emerging Markets Fund, Inc. since December 2007 and serves as its Independent Director. She has been an Independent Director of Hess Corporation since 1993. She has been an Independent Director at Canadian National Railway Company since June 1, 2001. She serves as a Director/Trustee of various investment companies in the Franklin Templeton Group of funds. She has been a Trustee of Franklin Custodian Fund, Inc since 1976 and Franklin Income Fund since 1998. She serves as the Lead Independent Trustee of 143 portfolios in the fund complex of Franklin and Templeton Funds. She has been Lead Independent Director at Templeton Growth Fund, Inc. Templeton Dragon Fund, Inc. , Templeton Russia and East European Fund, Inc. and Franklin Templeton Investments Funds - Templeton Global Smaller Companies Fund since 2007. She has been Lead Independent Trustee at Templeton Emerging Markets Fund, Templeton Emerging Markets Income Fund and Templeton Global Income Fund since December 2007. She has been Lead Independent Trustee of Templeton Global Income Fund since December 2007 and its Independent Trustee since 1996. She has been a Director of Santander Consumer USA Holdings Inc since November 29, 2016. She serves as an Operating Trustee of TWE Holdings I, II and III Trusts. She served as Lead Independent Director and Director of Templeton Russia and East European Fund Inc since 2007 and 1996 respectively. She serves as a Member of the Board of Governors at Investment Company Institute. She has been Independent Trustee at Franklin Custodian Funds since 1998. She has been Independent Director at Franklin Federal Tax-Free Income Fund since September 2005. She has been Independent Trustee at Templeton Funds Retirement Annuity Separate Account since June 2005. She has been Independent Trustee at Franklin Limited Duration Income Trust since 2007. She has been Independent Trustee at Templeton China World Fund since 1996. She has been Trustee at Franklin Investors Securities Trust - Franklin Floating Rate Daily Access Fund since 1998. She has been Independent Trustee at Franklin Universal Trust since January 2004. She has been Independent Trustee at Franklin Investors Securities Trust - Franklin Equity Income Fund since 1996. She has been Trustee at Templeton Developing Markets Trust since 1996. She has been Trustee at Templeton Institutional Funds and its Funds Complex since 1996. She has been Director at Templeton Institutional Funds - International Equity Series since 1996. She has been Director at Templeton Funds - Templeton Foreign Fund and Templeton Funds - Templeton World Fund since 1996. She has been Director at Franklin Strategic Series Funds and Its Funds Complex since 1996. She has been Director at Franklin Investors Securities Trust - Franklin Total Return Fund since 1996. She has been Director at Franklin Global Trust Funds since 1996. She serves as Trustee at Franklin Strategic Series - Franklin Natural Resources Fund. She served as a Director of Hercules Inc. since 1993. She served as a Director of RTI International Metals, Inc. from July 29, 1999 to July 23, 2015. She served as a Director of Franklin Capital Growth Fund since 1996. She served as an Independent Director of Hawk Acquisition Intermediate Corporation II from 1994 to June 2013. She served as a Trustee of Templeton Global Govt. since 1996 and Franklin Multi-Income Trust since January 2004. She served as an Independent Director of H. J. Heinz Company from 1994 to June 7, 2013. She served as Director at The Kraft Heinz Foods Company until June 7, 2013. She served as Director of Franklin Templeton International Trust since 1996. She served as Independent Trustee at Franklin Global Trust Funds since 1996. She served as Franklin Global Trust Funds since 1996. She has been Independent Trustee at Franklin Gold and Precious Metals Fund since 1996. She served as Director at Institutional Fiduciary Trust since 1996. She served as Trustee at Templeton Capital Accumulator Fund since 2000. She served as Director at RTI International Metals, Inc. since July 29, 1999 until July 23, 2015. She served as an Independent Director at Kraft Heinz Intermediate Corporation II since 1994 until June 2013. She served as a Director of Digex, Incorporated since November 2001 and Franklin Global Communications Fund since 1996. She served as a Director of Beverly and Golden Living Centers (Formerly known as Beverly Enterprises, Inc.) from 1995 to May 2004. She is a Member of the State Bars of Florida, Georgia and the District of Columbia. She is the recipient of the Secretary of the Treasury's highest award, the Alexander Hamilton Award. She is an Attorney. She holds a B.S. and J.D. degrees from the University of Florida.Read Full Background




